					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/veiedhimaedhr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3737554); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3737554&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226171" alt="Veiedhimaedhr" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3737554)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/veiedhimaedhr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3737554); return false;" >Veiedhimaedhr</a></span> <span class="odate time_1527905630 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jun 2018 02:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3820713">
									

<p>For some behind the scenes action with the Omega-K Family:</p>
<p>Before the brain transplants there was the talk about brains. What to do with em? Eventually, it came down to two options. Brain swapping through wave transfer, or through surgery. After team-member Galaxy-Class mysteriously vanished, I took on the role of figuring out what to do with de brainz. Time passes and here we are.</p>
<p>Narratively, this is done for emotional impact as well as imagery. There's more to play with and a lot more to tie in with some of the themes of this team.</p>
<p>In-Universe, the reason is $. Repairing the same body as it ages through point DNA modifications and so on is more expensive than what is essentially a hackjob+lego. Furthermore, repairing a body gives you youth back, but also YOUR youth back. Wouldn't you rather want something different? And if you have the money why wait? You can easily just change into something more&#8230;experimental.</p>
<p>In any case, I hope you enjoyed the piece!</p>

							</div>

								
					
