														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3828502">
									

<p>Prometheus labs has access to superscience, so maybe they <em>could</em> build a robot body that would be compatible with a biological human brain, but it would probably be cheaper and easier to grow clones and prevent their brains from developing (and even cheaper and easier to just grow regular clones and chop their brains out).</p>
<p>Think about how much harder it is to make an egg or an apple artificially than it is to just grow them, then scale that up to a whole human body. I'm not saying these fictional superscientists couldn't do it, just that it would be a pretty differnt thing at that point.</p>

							</div>

								
					
